title: Grateful Dead Live at Olympia Theater on 1972-05-04
taper: Betty Cantor and Tim Dalton and Harvey Lubar
description:
Set 1

Greatest Story Ever Told, Deal, Mr. Charlie, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women, Chinatown Shuffle, Playin' In The Band, You Win Again, It Hurts Me Too, He's Gone, El Paso, Big Railroad Blues, Two Souls In Communion, Casey Jones

Set 2

Good Lovin', Next Time You See Me, Ramble On Rose, Jack Straw, Dark Star-> Drums-> Dark Star-> Sugar Magnolia, Sing Me Back Home, Mexicali Blues, Big Boss Man, Uncle John's Band, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

5/4/72 was one of the "Honeymoon" tapes that were taken from David Gans'house while he was away on his honeymoon.

reviews.review_text:
No Reviews on This Show? WTF? Another complete gem from the Europe '72 tour.

Please everyone take a listen to this immaculate recording of Pig's "Two Souls in Communion" (The Stranger).

It is just about flawless and rips me up every time I hear it. You can hear Pig's heart was totally in the moment despite the ravaged condition of his body.

Long live the Dead!
